  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The treatment of older patients with acute myeloid leukemia that is secondary to previous
      myelodysplastic syndrome, myeloproliferative neoplasm, or prior cytotoxic exposure remains
      unsatisfactory. We compared patients treated with intensive chemotherapy or azacitidine
      within two centres.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
